  "prompt": "What does \"designation\" mean on a form?",
  "response": "The term \"designation\" on a form typically refers to a title, label, or specific classification that identifies a person\u2019s role, position, or status. For example, in a job application, it might refer to the job title you are applying for or your current position. In other contexts, it might specify a particular category or designation related to professional qualifications, such as \"Certified Public Accountant\" (CPA) or \"Project Manager.\" Essentially, it helps to clarify the function or title of an individual in a particular context.",
